claim.claim-text:
9. An acrylate ester polymer blend consisting essentially of 1) from about 95% by weight to about 50% by weight of a poly(methyl methacrylate) based polymer comprising (a) from about 80% by weight to 100% by weight of methyl methacrylate, and (b) from about 0% by weight to about 20 weight % of a copolymerizable free-radical polymerizable comonomer, 2) from about 5% by weight to about 50% by weight of a copolymer consisting essentially of the pyrolysis product of a copolymer consisting essentially of (a) from about 50% by weight to about 95% by weight of methyl methacrylate, (b) from about 5% by weight to about 30% by weight of t-butyl methacrylate, and (c) from about 0% by weight to about 20% by weight of a copolymerizable lower (meth)acrylate ester monomer;
said pyrolysis product copolymer having a refractive index compatible with that of said poly(methyl methacrylate based copolymer;
3) from about 0% by weight to about 50% by weight of an refractive index compatible impact modifier polymer material.
